<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p><rs type="criteria">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">sarcophagus</rs> <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.95</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.81</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.78</measure> with a central <rs type="decoration">tabella ansata</rs>, supported by <rs type="decoration">putti</rs>. On either side, <rs type="decoration">garland</rs>s, with a <rs type="decoration">bust</rs> above.
See further Isik, loc. cit.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p>a. <rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> around the <rs type="decoration">bust</rs> to the left, b. around the bust to the right, c. on the <rs type="decoration">tabella</rs>; inscription c. must have begun on the lid.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p> Quite nicely designed in the second-to-fourth-century style, reasonably well cut, fairly well aligned, <measure precision="circa" type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.02</measure>; ligatured <foreign lang="grc">ΗΝ</foreign> (c. l.7), <foreign lang="grc">ΤΕ</foreign> (c. l.3), <foreign lang="grc">ΤΗΝ</foreign> (c. l.7); unconventional spelling in a, l.2.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
Probably  <date notBefore="0234" notAfter="0267" exact="none" cert="low">middle third century A.D.</date>
 (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">nomenclature</rs>).</p>
</div>
